<p class="paragraph-text">He is also hailed as the first great American conductor; notably, he was the first American to conduct at <a href="/artists/anna-netrebko/returns-la-scala-russian-opera/">La Scala</a> and to lead a major US symphony orchestra – in his case, the New York Philharmonic.</p><p class="paragraph-text">The conductor is also credited with bringing the music of <a href="/composers/mahler/">Gustav Mahler</a> into the mainstream. He recorded all of the symphonies twice in what would be termed the Bernstein-Mahler cycle, and conducted all of the works in concert too. </p><p class="paragraph-text">Bernstein achieved an impressive array of distinctions during his career, including 16 Grammy Awards, seven Emmys, two Tonys and a Kennedy Center Honour. </p><p class="paragraph-text"><strong>Read more: </strong><a href="/composers/bernstein-l/maestro-netflix-biopic-cast-plot-release-date/"><strong>Maestro: everything to know about Bradley Cooper’s upcoming Bernstein biopic on Netflix</strong></a></p>
<div class="video-container">
